snippet.textDisplay: I think I agree the most with Roz than any other YouTuber or Rotten Tomato critic. It is somewhat flawed in that solutions to problems and challenges don’t seem to need anything out of the characters to find, almost like they snap their fingers and it’s just given to them. But I think the film really invokes the original trilogy and I really enjoyed the final act of the film. I loved seeing Luke in a form where he actually seems like himself and of course Han Solo was epic and unexpected. Hearing the voices of many of the Jedi from the prequels and even Clone Wars/Rebels was incredible. The film manages to tie up a lot of loose ends that Episode 8 left unanswered and the ending of the film is absolutely beautiful. With what JJ had to work with after TLJ, I think he did an amazing job bringing back the true spirit of Star Wars and finally giving the fans what they wanted and deserved.
snippet.textOriginal: I think I agree the most with Roz than any other YouTuber or Rotten Tomato critic. It is somewhat flawed in that solutions to problems and challenges don’t seem to need anything out of the characters to find, almost like they snap their fingers and it’s just given to them. But I think the film really invokes the original trilogy and I really enjoyed the final act of the film. I loved seeing Luke in a form where he actually seems like himself and of course Han Solo was epic and unexpected. Hearing the voices of many of the Jedi from the prequels and even Clone Wars/Rebels was incredible. The film manages to tie up a lot of loose ends that Episode 8 left unanswered and the ending of the film is absolutely beautiful. With what JJ had to work with after TLJ, I think he did an amazing job bringing back the true spirit of Star Wars and finally giving the fans what they wanted and deserved.

snippet.textDisplay:
live and work in Greece so the movie is out...This is an absolute & complete mess and yes it is a trainwreck! For several weeks now, I've been over critical as I made it very clear that Disney, from the beginning of Force Awakens & Last Jedi you've already screwed big time! I'm a firm believer, if Disney and Lucasfilm would have entertained the idea of using the Expanded Universe stories of "Heir to the Empire", "Dark Force Rising" and "Last Command" series. It would have been a whole lot better! Expanded Universe definitely had a better storyline than the crap we were forced to accept with episode 7 & 8!

I will not lend any spoilers here in this comment but as many have reported this movie has gone through so much trimming that you can actually tell the two different directors that this film had trying to tell two different sides. I didn't walk out like other fans did. I can't believe I saw this movie as a Star Wars fan. Hell all I can say is that I rather watch Transformers Last Knight 10 times rather than to watch this movie twice. Smh!

I walked out feeling like Disney wasted the time of the fans and not to mention my money. Disney also disrespect the original actors of Mark, Harrison and now the late Carrie in the garbage of episode 7 & 8 movies. We now do not have Han or Leia alive to even fix all this Disney screw ups. 155 minutes movie with only 12 minutes of the Emperor Palptine storyline. Mace Windu lines is 5 words only, no Qui Gon Jinn.

The movie insults the legacy of Anakin, Leia and Luke by calling this Rise of Skywalker, when it should be "Rise of Rey Skywalker per Kathleen. Smh! Kathleen Kennedy, you had the shots deleted of having all the Force ghosts, the new Generation of Jedi, Kylo death and redemption, you had a backstory for Palptine survival of the 2nd death star. So in this movie Anakin is no longer the chosen one and Luke was treated like crap in these last 3 movies. Kathleen you had shots with Rey and Ben (Anakin) Solo being the Masters. Many important and solid pieces that George Lucas directed are now on the cutting floor! Why!? Oh Kathleen!

Again, in Greece it has already opened and it's worth a 56% or less in Rotten Tomatoes! To me JJ didn't fix the previous two garbage movies of 7 & 8! Mark Hamill has already tweeted not to waste your money and wait until it comes out on cable TV.

Wow! Rise of Rey Skywalker per Kathleen Kennedy is all about Marketing and the Merchandising & toys! Wow it's a not about the fans it's all about MONEY!

But it's sad to know that George Lucas had some input in how the ending should be like and it was scratched. Thanks Disney!! For now, the movie seems to be everywhere without a solid storyline AGAIN! 155 minutes movie has everything crammed up to a result of a Nightmare & a Trainwreck of a movie! Yes it feels like 6 movies all wrapped in one. It jumps around a lot and misses a lot of information and never answers questions the fans have. George didn't do this but Disney did and this Kennedy woman produced this trash. I did see fans walk out at the too obvious and typical ending. I was highly disappointed in this movie. This movie never answered my question on who the kid is or was, from the Last Jedi that uses the Force to hand him the broom over to sweep. I wanted to know who this young kid in the Last Jedi was but nevermind! No purpose of this kid the last scene of Last Jedi!

Anyways, Anakin, Obi Won scenes were cheated and not to have Qui Gon Jinn at least make a small cameo. The Jedi responsible for all these Force ghosts coming back! Kathleen is an idiot!

The last scene of Rise of Skywalker as Rey stands in the iconic pose in front of the twin suns in Tatooine is a slap on the face for George Lucas and Luke Skywalker! Kathleen has taken our great Star Wars experience that began in 1977 and flushed it down the Walt Disney golden toilet!

Nevertheless, Good luck Disney with the Rise of Rey Yellow Blade Lightsaber Skywalker! But as for me and I am sorry to say that this is a waste of time and money for the true fans!

Kathleen to JJ and George Lucas memo! Look "Star Wars Rise of Disney Money Maker" is all about money $$$, merchandise and toys! So screw the fans!

Love & Yours always

Kathleen Kennedy!
